 <div id="moreinfo">

  <h1>What does Yoop.ly do?</h1><p class="bodyText">Yooply makes discipline management <strong>easier</strong> and <strong>more effective</strong>. Admins love that it cuts down on paperwork and centralizes all the behavior data, from student statements to detention minutes. </p> <p class="bodyText">Teachers can <strong>quickly</strong> send their referrals straight from their smartphones and keep track of  discipline outcomes. No more wondering where their students went. </p><p class="bodyText">Students can record their incident reports, write reflections, and give each other <strong>positive</strong> feedback, all from their mobiles, an office computer, or any device with an internet browser. </p>
</div>


 <div id="admindiv">
<img id="mainimage" src="/images/disciplineshouldnt.png"  alt="Admins using Yooply" title="This app was built by teachers adn admins to meet school needs" width="100%" >
</div>




<div id="moreinfo">
<h2>No more running around</h2>
		<p class="bodyText">Admins can also manage and track detention minutes, student contracts, suspensions, notify parents and keep all teachers informed. No more clipboards, no more clunky spreadsheets or desktop software everyone hates.   </p>

		<h2>Let's stay positive!</h2>
		<p class="bodyText"> With Yooply, students can send each other positive messages, earn points and rewards,  unlock features and monitor their own behavior. Teachers can award positive behavior points customized to your school's reward system. </p>

		<h2>Real time data</h2>
		<p class="bodyText">Keeping track of student data and discipline trends is easy. Teachers, admins, parents and students can monitor school behavior stats and make better decisions that ultimately impact learning.</p>

		<h2>Customize</h2>
		<p class="bodyText">Schools can tailor Yoop.ly to fit their discipline plans. Add your own consequences, rewards, and discipline tags to match your state, district, or school requirements.  </p>
		<h2>Discipline Matters</h2>
		<p class="bodyText">The poor management of school discipline is one of two main reasons teachers leave their schools. Students and teachers consistently rate discipline issues as a major obstacle to effective learning. When behavior systems are ineffective or poorly enforced, it makes it hard to create a positive and effective learning environment.  </p>

